div.h1: Interrupt Stack Frame: CPU-Pushed vs. Handler-Pushed

div.p: Key Insight: The stack grows downward. CPU pushes first (lowest addresses), handler pushes on top. IRET expects the stack pointer to be at the saved EIP position.
If CPL changes (CS.RPL CPL): 4. ESP [ESP+12] 5. SS [ESP+16]
Handler must adjust ESP to point at saved EIP before executing iret!
Workaround: Stub pushes dummy 0 for exceptions without error codes uniform stack frame
Pass ESP to C handler: asm push esp call c_interrupt_handler
